FT  02 APR 94 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
Gold shares in Johannesburg recorded small gains following a rise in the
price of bullion, while industrials moved lower as political tension
continued. There was little direct reaction to the state of emergency
declared in Natal.
The overall index rose 2 to 4,937, industrials slipped 50 to 5,644 and gold
strengthened 18 to 2,012.
De Beers put on R1.25 to R105 and Anglos R1 to R202. In golds, marginals
made some of the steepest gains. Doorns added 15 cents to R2.75 and Loraine
45 cents to R15.25.
